Oct 12 2009	An Actual Bargain in London!	I had the pleasure of spending 4 nights at this chain hotel during a recent European tour with a student travel group. The price of the hotel was part of the tour package so of course, my opinion of the value is a bit skewed. But as far as the facilities themselves, I was pleasantly surprised. On previous London group tours I usually found myself in accomodations akin to &quot;The Royal Windsor Arms&quot; in &quot;National Lampoon's European Vacation&quot;. This Days Inn was the usual cookiecutter American-style building, but featured modest-sized clean rooms, a fantastic breakfast and wonder of wonders, an ice machine. Rooms were clean, bathrooms maintained and the TV worked perfectly. The staff was accessible and helpful. The location is just one block from Lambeth North Underground station and a short stroll away from the free War Museum.The only minor criticism is the lack of A/C but that is par for the course in Europe. At least an electric fan is available in each room.	
