Jun 13 2009 	An American hotel in London	This was a pretty decent hotel for the money. We got a great deal through Expedia (about $100 a night for a double room w/ bathroom). The hotel is reminiscent of a United States budget hotel. However, in London, that gave us some nice amenities such as a larger than average room, roomy bathroom, and an ice machine (rare in Europe!). The amenities were above par - comfortable bed, nice tv, fan in the room, blow dryer, nice shower, etc. The location of the hotel isn't spectacular. It is on the southbank, near the Lambeth north tube stop. The only tube line that travels to that station is the Bakerloo, one of my least favorite lines to use. The waterloo station is a bit farther away but gives you access to the Bakerloo and Northern lines. One plus of being on the southbank however is the fact that things (for the most part) are cheaper. Instead of eating the hotel's pricey 7 pound/person breakfast, I would recommend finding something to eat locally. There is a great bakery called Gregg's by the waterloo station. One downside of the hotel was the staff. Though we only had to interact with them a handful of times, their English was poor and they were not friendly. The internet was good but a bit costly. Overall, if you can get a good price, this hotel is worth it.	
